WEBVTT

00:00.697 --> 00:01.596
<i>Previously on "Heartland"...</i>

00:01.698 --> 00:03.598
I am entitled to say,
Ty Borden,

00:03.700 --> 00:06.134
that you have completed
your probation period successfully.

00:06.236 --> 00:06.964
Thanks.

00:07.071 --> 00:08.402
Good luck with the rest of your life.

00:08.505 --> 00:09.836
- I'm telling you the truth.
- Yeah.

00:09.940 --> 00:12.272
You and Ashley alone all night
just talking.

00:12.376 --> 00:13.172
Yeah.

00:13.277 --> 00:14.938
He's the only guy
that really gets me, you know?

00:15.045 --> 00:18.708
Getting what he wants
is probably closer to the truth.

00:18.816 --> 00:20.249
Amy.

00:20.384 --> 00:23.012
- Don't talk to me, Caleb.
- It's not what it looks like.

00:23.754 --> 00:26.086
Bedford Oil could build a pump
right there,

00:26.190 --> 00:27.919
and there'd be nothing
you could do about it.

00:28.025 --> 00:28.923
Oh, yes, there is.

00:29.026 --> 00:31.290
Hi. P.W. Morris.

00:35.833 --> 00:37.630
You are supposed to be Peter.

00:38.769 --> 00:40.259
You own Bedford Oil.

00:40.370 --> 00:41.359
Yeah.

00:41.472 --> 00:42.666
This can never work.

00:42.773 --> 00:44.707
You stand for things
that make my blood boil.

00:44.808 --> 00:46.901
- Keep things interesting, right?
- Good-bye.

00:51.381 --> 00:53.906
Okay. Try it now.

00:56.386 --> 00:59.116
Hey! There you go.

00:59.223 --> 01:01.191
Awesome. Good as new.

01:01.358 --> 01:02.882
Your dad was right
about the condenser.

01:02.993 --> 01:05.553
Well, there's two things
my dad knows everything about.

01:05.662 --> 01:07.755
Cows and cars.

01:07.865 --> 01:09.457
Hey, thanks for your help, Amy.

01:09.600 --> 01:10.862
All I did was turn the key.

01:10.968 --> 01:14.597
You know what?
We should pimp this baby up, hmm?

01:14.705 --> 01:16.764
Spoiler. Neon lights. Come on.

01:16.874 --> 01:18.398
- I don't know.
- Supercharge the engine.

01:18.509 --> 01:19.737
Chicks dig the truck the way it is.

01:19.910 --> 01:22.105
Oh, they do, do they?

01:24.581 --> 01:27.880
Hey, Ty. Clint's here.
We should probably go inside.

01:27.985 --> 01:28.713
Who's Clint?

01:29.987 --> 01:32.717
- Ty's old pro...
- Professional wrestler.

01:33.991 --> 01:35.219
A wrestler?

01:35.325 --> 01:36.917
Well, he's an old friend
from Calgary.

01:37.027 --> 01:39.962
He used to wrestle.

01:41.165 --> 01:44.464
Well, I should probably get going.
I'll see you tonight.

01:50.207 --> 01:52.767
So, I trust Lou
got you and the kids

01:52.876 --> 01:55.344
settled into the dude ranch
okay last night.

01:55.445 --> 01:56.776
She did, Jack, thanks.

01:56.880 --> 01:58.074
What's this?

01:58.182 --> 02:00.173
Well, when you're dealing
with kids on probation,

02:00.284 --> 02:02.309
it's very important
to stick to a schedule.

02:02.419 --> 02:03.977
Now, this weekend in the country,

02:04.087 --> 02:06.248
it isn't just about,
you know, having fun.

02:06.356 --> 02:08.687
It's about rehabilitation,
reintegration.

02:08.792 --> 02:12.193
This is very comprehensive.

02:12.296 --> 02:13.194
Well, yeah.

02:13.330 --> 02:15.059
I didn't want to leave
anything to chance.

02:15.165 --> 02:16.757
You know,
these kids need structure.

02:16.867 --> 02:18.732
It's all part of what
the new probation is all about.

02:19.136 --> 02:19.898
Right.

02:20.003 --> 02:22.938
Well, we will certainly do our best
to stick to your schedule.

02:23.040 --> 02:25.235
But do you really think
it was a good idea

02:25.342 --> 02:27.435
to leave those kids out there
all on their own,

02:27.544 --> 02:29.739
you know, unsupervised?

02:29.846 --> 02:30.870
Don't worry, Lou.

02:30.981 --> 02:32.471
They were fast asleep
when I left them.

02:32.583 --> 02:35.074
And besides, they're way out
in the middle of nowhere.

02:35.185 --> 02:37.653
What trouble could
they possibly get into?

